originalText.text: BEWARE!  The owner is very disrepectful, a liar, and unprofessional.  I was a monthly parking customer.  On June 7th 2021, one of their employees drove a commercial van of another customer into my 2019 Tesla model 3.  This was not a simple fender bender accident.  I understand accidents do happen but it's how it was handled and taken care of by the owner of the lot.  Bascially, the owner did not finish the repair on the car.  He told me to get a quote for the damages on the vehicle.  I got an estimate from a authorized Tesla body shop and gave it to the owner.  The owner diregarded the quote from Tesla and told me he would take it to a body shop that he knows.  I did not agree but he did it anways.  The owner fixed the dents and scratches using a body shop he chose, however the repair was not complete.  There was a whistle sound coming from the right driver side still when driving at high speed.  We told the employees and the owner about a whistle sound that was coming from the right driver side the next morning after the accident had occured.  When I told the owner of the parking lot that the repair was not finished, he stated, "how do i know it was not like that before the accident."  He refused to accept responsiblilty and told me not to park there anymore. The additional repair is costing $550. I have no idea how anyone in NYC can run his business this way and stay in business. Very rude, very unprofesionnal and canaiving.  Park at your own risk.

originalText.text: Parked here for the day when I had a work meeting nearby. We had driven through a snow storm on the way down from Canada, so the car was gross. I noticed the workers washing other cars and asked if we could get our van washed while it was there.  Y’all, our car is cleaner than it was when we pulled it off the lot. They vacuumed, they got the nasty salt off it, I think they honestly got rust off our snow tires. It was awesome. Parking costs $35 for 24 hours.
